data:
T stage is determined by the size of the tumor.
T1 stage: tumor size up to 2.0 cm
T2 stage: tumor size between 2.0 cm and 5.0 cm
T3 stage: tumor size greater than 5.0 cm
T4 stage: tumor of any size with direct extension to the chest wall or skin
T stage is determined by the largest dimension of the tumor, not the distance from the margin

The T stage is not affected by the number of positive lymph nodes
